'''Khamaseen''' is a mini-[[hurrican]]e type [[wind]] that is common in [[Egypt]] and [[Sudan]] towards the end of [[March]] and [[April]] of each year.  Hot weather ensues, as well as [[sandstorm]]s.

According to the ''Turkish Calendar of Storms'' a storm of three days, to be expected around [[February 1]].

